properties.name: Louisa Boren Park
properties.location_description: Start/End point, 15th Avenue E and E Garfield Street, eastern edge of the park
properties.rhetorical_usage: hidden little treasure, great views out to Lake Washington, Union Bay, and the Cascade Mountains

properties.name: Grand Army of the Republic Cemetery
properties.location_description: North side of E Howe Street, west of 15th Ave E, east of Federal Ave E
properties.rhetorical_usage: cemetery for Union veterans, 526 graves

properties.name: Streissguth Gardens
properties.location_description: Off E Blaine Street, between Federal Ave E and 10th Ave E, reached by descending steps
properties.rhetorical_usage: little urban oasis

properties.name: Former John and Eliza Leary House (Office of the Bishop)
properties.location_description: East side of 10th Avenue E, between E Blaine St and E Highland Dr
properties.rhetorical_usage: grand building, lovely sandstone, famous features like Tiffany windows (formerly)

properties.name: Former Pierre Ferry House
properties.location_description: Next door south of the Former Leary House on 10th Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: area historically known as "owl hollow", features carved wooden owls and sculptures

properties.name: Former Sam Hill Mansion
properties.location_description: North side of E Highland Drive, west of Broadway E
properties.rhetorical_usage: built in 1908, featured rooftop garden, in-room telephones, 10ft thick walls

properties.name: Former Horace Chapin Henry Property (Future Public Space)
properties.location_description: Northwest corner of Harvard Avenue E and E Prospect Street
properties.rhetorical_usage: originally a 1.6-acre estate, future public space

properties.name: Harvard-Belmont Historic District
properties.location_description: Area roughly bounded by E Highland Drive, Belmont Avenue E, E Roy Street, and Broadway E
properties.rhetorical_usage: heart of the federally and city designated district, premier location for wealthy homes

properties.name: Garry Oak (Oregon White Oak)
properties.location_description: Corner of Belmont Place E and Belmont Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: large and unusual tree, Washington's lone native oak, rare this far north

properties.name: Former Nellie Cornish School Building (Kerry Hall)
properties.location_description: On E Roy Street, near Boylston Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: original location of Cornish College of the Arts, building features names of famous artists

properties.name: Daughters of the American Revolution (DAR) House
properties.location_description: East side of Harvard Avenue E on E Roy Street
properties.rhetorical_usage: copy of George Washington's home, Mount Vernon

properties.name: Small Public Space (SW corner Roy & Harvard)
properties.location_description: Southwest corner of E Roy Street and Harvard Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: features benches with terra-cotta elements, tile with architectural drawing and quote

properties.name: Former Woman's Century Club (Harvard Exit)
properties.location_description: Southeast corner of E Roy Street and Harvard Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: club founded in 1891, building housed Harvard Exit movie theater

properties.name: Arthur Loveless Building
properties.location_description: On the north side of E Roy Street, east of Broadway E
properties.rhetorical_usage: handsome two-story building, described as "a little bit of England", centered on a private courtyard

properties.name: Frederick Anhalt Apartments
properties.location_description: Along E Roy Street, east of Broadway E
properties.rhetorical_usage: elegant Capitol Hill apartments, French Norman-inspired elements

properties.name: Maryland Apartments
properties.location_description: On E Roy Street, before reaching 13th Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: city-designated landmark built in 1910

properties.name: Millionaire's Row (14th Ave E)
properties.location_description: Along 14th Avenue E, starting at E Roy Street
properties.rhetorical_usage: known for Seattle's finest early 20th-century homes

properties.name: Granite Hitching Post (Millionaire's Row)
properties.location_description: Southwest corner of E Roy Street and 14th Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: rare sign of early Seattle's equestrian history

properties.name: Elbridge Amos Stuart Stepping Stone
properties.location_description: Southeast corner of E Valley Street and 14th Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: low granite block used for stepping from horse-drawn carriages

properties.name: James A. Moore Mansion
properties.location_description: Southwest corner of E Aloha Street and 14th Avenue E
properties.rhetorical_usage: brick mansion built in 1903, home of Capitol Hill's developer

properties.name: Volunteer Park Water Tower (Stand Pipe)
properties.location_description: Within Volunteer Park, near E Prospect St and 14th Ave E
properties.rhetorical_usage: brick water tower built in 1906, observation area with views

properties.name: Seattle Asian Art Museum (Former SAM)
properties.location_description: Within Volunteer Park, north of the Water Tower
properties.rhetorical_usage: original Seattle Art Museum, opened 1933, progressive design, now houses Asian Art

properties.name: Volunteer Park Conservatory
properties.location_description: Within Volunteer Park, north of the Seattle Asian Art Museum
properties.rhetorical_usage: opened in 1912, design based on London's Crystal Palace, houses extensive plant collection

properties.name: Concrete Trolley Retaining Wall
properties.location_description: Along 15th Avenue E, near Volunteer Park
properties.rhetorical_usage: remnant of the former streetcar system, blocks with holes where rails sat

properties.name: Lake View Cemetery
properties.location_description: West side of 15th Avenue E, opposite Volunteer Park
properties.rhetorical_usage: one of the oldest and most diverse cemeteries, graves of early settlers and notable figures
